.<br>/cast 1 <br>fizzle <br>/cast 1 <br>fizzle <br>/say OH SHIT<br>/cast 1<br>BAM BAM BAM <br>Loading Please wait...<br>Being 4am and work bright and early in the morning I gave up defeated for the night.  <br><br>My question is has anybody successfully done this? Any tips on the timing from ....<br>Target out of range usin flux staff, till you blast? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Alphie Bits<br>GNOME wizzy<br>Mith Marr<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyilar44.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yilar44</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/19/02 5:23:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=280.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forget quading...multi kiting?</span><hr size=1> well if whole zone is up.. i guess you could try with some Al'kabor spell which doesn't have a max targets. Then start in tower by click as many as you can, run around clikc everything else you see (except Yvolcarn and drakes) and then round them ALL up and use spamstick to see if range is good enough (remember they have to be oor for a while)... don't know if it works...<br><br>Other option is to bring in a Chanter and stun the whole zone <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and use PBAoE tactics <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43436>Yilar</a> <br>60 Sorcerer <br> Mith Marr  <br><a href=http://www.forsakenrealm.org/index.asp>Forsaken Realm</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/21/02 10:51:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=280.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forget quading...multi kiting?</span><hr size=1> Al'Kabor spells have a max of 5 targets. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 35th Season<br>Guild Leader of Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27902" target="_blank">Look down my pants with Magelo!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugvivis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gvivis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/22/02 8:21:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=280.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forget quading...multi kiting?</span><hr size=1> it won't work well.  i pulled lot of orc in crushbone, because of 4 mob rule, most of them would walk away from my jyll range by time i cast it.  you will need a chanter.<br><br>there is a post in aoe forum show a possible setup (wiz/healer) without enchanter. but it really risky, and might not work well with wyvern. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukaeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kaeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/26/02 8:13:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=280.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forget quading...multi kiting?</span><hr size=1> Yea a while back with my first wizzie(sis deleted him) I was in warrens and a train was pulled I had alkabor up so I let it lose and counted dmg for somewhere in 250+=) think they changed it so that alkabors is no longer unlimited. I had rememberd that and wanted to try it with beetles in NK and I hit 5 out of the 20 I had rounded up..oh well quading beetles is still fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utorcerarcana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Torcer Arcana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/27/02 7:49:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=280.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forget quading...multi kiting?</span><hr size=1> You are Insane! - I love your Chutzpah though! <p>Norrath: Torcer Arcana - Level 57 Wizard - The Nameless<Br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/upyanfir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pyanfir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/28/02 1:12:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=280.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forget quading...multi kiting?</span><hr size=1> I don't really think this is feasable solo ...<br><br>I have managed to pull and AoE all of crushbone a few times, but it generally takes two casts to get every last one of them (if I don't pull TR and friends) simply because of aggro rules.<br><br>It's all about timing ... frankly, I don't think one would survive the hit from the wyverns after the first cast, even if you timed it right and hit them all with the first shot.<br><br>I may try it tho ... be a fun challenge if nothing else.<br><br>Pyan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uthediscoinferno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The DiscoInferno</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/28/02 11:37:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=280.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forget quading...multi kiting?</span><hr size=1> PB AE's require melee range =\  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/upyanfir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pyanfir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/29/02 10:11:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=280.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forget quading...multi kiting?</span><hr size=1> Aye Disco, hence the timing aspect ... you have to round everyone up, then time the cast so that it hits JUST as the mobs reach melee range.<br><br>Easy to do, and pretty safe with low greens - not sure about even low blues tho ... Let alone having to do it more than once to get them all dead.<br><br>P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufleviuskot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>flevius KoT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/25/02 11:10:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=280.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> doubt this'd work</span><hr size=1> You're looking at taking a lot of hits even if you time it perfectly, and getting stunned would kill you quick.  Looking at sp.dat info, winds of gelid has a 35 foot radius compared to 25 on jylls, but I don't think the extra 10 feet would be enough.<br><br>Flev <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uabadacus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Abadacus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/25/02 2:53:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=280.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Your best bet...</span><hr size=1> I have tried the idea out before and it does work, but you have to think &quot;Outside the Box&quot;, so to speak.<br><br>What I mean by that is to use the world geometry to your favor.  A couple of things first....<br><br>The only worthwhile spells to use would be Winds of Gelid and SuperNova, as they do indeed have the extra radius.  Jyll's won't work well enough for it to be effective in this case.<br><br>Wyverns are actually a good mob to try them on because you have plenty of them, assuming they are not camped, are light blue to a 60, and you have plenty of room to negotiate a pull.  But most importantly, you have a cliff, that you can climb easily enough using Levitation.<br><br>The idea is this:  Pull and bunch up the Wyverns on the beach, but giving yourself enough time to climb the cliff before they have a chance to reach it.  You must be stopped at the cliff edge or slightly beyong it before the Wyverns reach the bottom portion of the cliff.  Put yourself in 3rd person view, so that you can see the cliff face, and the mobs following you.  What this does is simple, it gives you time to cast your spell when you know they are approaching your range, but still have the physical distance to travel to reach you (straight up the cliff).  You must be far enough from the cliff face to prevent melee damage, and close enough for the spell to take effect (6 seconds for both Super Nova and Winds of Gelid).  <br><br>Regardless of whether it works or not, you will have to reposition the mobs for every cast of SN and WoG, as there is a significant recast delay, and one nuke will not take them out.  Also, Winds of Gelid is cold based, so may present a problem with Wyverns.  I don't hunt them, but seems to me that they may be cold resistant.  That and both spells are very high in mana cost.<br><br>I have not tried farting around with the Wyverns yet, though likely to do so just to test out my tactic in the near future.  See if this works for you.  You will need good timing, a good connection, and most importantly, Gnomish balls of Steel to pull it off.<br><br>Abadacus RuneMaster<br>Gnomish Sorceror<br>Afterlife <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=280.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showNextMessage?topi